<chapter xml:id="ChapProb" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Probability </title>

  <introduction>
    <p> In this chapter we will investigate some basic probability concepts. We will begin with a brief review of what probability is, how to use a tree diagram to determine the number outcomes, and discuss common rules for compound events. We will extend this to discrete probability distributions. </p>
  </introduction>
<objectives>
        <introduction>
          <p> At the end of this chapter, you will be able to:   </p>
        </introduction>
        <ol>
          <li> <p> Calculate the probability of simple events. </p> </li>
          <li> <p> Use the probability rules for OR, AND, GIVEN statements. </p> </li>
          <li> <p> Determine conditional probability. </p> </li>
          <li> <p> Use a tree diagram to determine the probability for multiple events. </p> </li>
          <li> <p> Calculate permutations and combinations. </p> </li>
          <li> <p> Determine the likelyhood of events from a probability distribution.  </p> </li>
          <li> <p> Evaluate a binomial distribution.  </p> </li>  
      </ol>
      </objectives>

